Test create some file and check

git log -1 (to check last commit)
git log --oneline (to check all commit in on line)
git log --grep "igmore"  (if dont know commit id )

BRANCH

git branch (Avaliable branch)
git branch branchname
git checkout branchname   (To switch branch)
git branch -d branchname (To delete branch)
GIT merge branchname (To merge branch) conflict (while merge if get conflict)

Git stashing (to stash an item only applies to modified file)

git stash (to stash an item)
git stash list
git stash apply stash@{0}  (to apply stashed item) add and commit
git stash clear (to clean stash)

git reset filename (code completed added to stg area if you want to add some info)
git reset .
git reset --hard (code completed added to stg area if you want to delete the file)

Git revert (code completed and added to stg and made a commit)
To undo the commit
git revert (commit-id) add ignore this

Remove untracked files git clean -n 
git clean -f

To apply tag
git tag -a tagname -m "message" commit-id
git tag (all tags)
git show tagname
git tag -d tagname

git clone url 

